# @nestjs-cipher

Production-grade NestJS encryption module with envelope encryption (AES-256-GCM) and KMS key wrapping.

## Project Structure

- `src/cipher-module/` — Core module implementation
  - `cipher-module.module.ts` — Dynamic module registration (forRoot, forRootAsync)
  - `cipher.service.ts` — Encryption/decryption with AES-256-GCM
  - `cipher.health.ts` — Health indicator for KMS provider
  - `interface.ts` — Types and injection token
  - `provider.service.ts` — KMS provider initialization
  - `providers/` — Provider implementations (GCP KMS)

## Development Standards

- **Language**: TypeScript 6+ with strict mode
- **Package manager**: pnpm 10.32+
- **Testing**: vitest
- **Linting**: xo + prettier
- **Commits**: Conventional commits (feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore)
- **Branch strategy**: Trunk-based development on main

## Running Locally

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm lint:fix    # Format and lint
pnpm build       # Compile TypeScript
pnpm test        # Run tests
```

## CI/CD

- **test.yml** — Runs tests on Node 24, 25 (push + PR)
- **lint.yml** — Runs xo linting (push + PR)
- **build.yml** — Compiles TypeScript (push + PR)
- **dependabot.yml** — Weekly dependency updates with conventional commit prefix

## Key Rules

- No console.log — use structured logging
- No hardcoded values — use config/interfaces
- Keep commits small and focused
- Always include tests with new features
- Update docs for breaking changes
